						               													<description>Summer is here and that means one thing for you and your crab buddies: Scuttleball! Scuttleball is just like volleyball but for crabs! You&amp;rsquo;ll need skill, luck, and guts if you want to win this tricky little dice game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Scuttleball is a 2-player dice-placement game that fits in a mint tin. Despite its small size, short rules, and bunch of dice, it offers a surprising amount of tense tactical moments and thematic tie-ins. At the beginning of each round, or volley, both players roll nine dice concealed behind their hands. Players alternate making a play on the ball by placing a die on their side of the court that exceeds the value of the last played die. The volley continues until one player can't make a play. Here's the exciting part: every space on the court has a special action that is activated when a die is placed. Actions are things like reroll a die, boost its value, or mirror an adjacent die. You&amp;rsquo;ll have to activate the right ability at the right time if you want to keep the volley going!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Scuttleball contains three different courts to accommodate different skill levels and game preferences: backyard (casual), beach (standard), or gymnasium (expert). There is also a free downloadable file to design your own court!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
